On Escalation Ticket # 00425524 the new comment has been added: Michael Burrofato:

@Salesforce @Chris Brooks @Ethan Israel  @Matthew Finnegan The screenshot provided shows the SP_DropTables job is also throwing a FK. This usually happens when running an older version of the analysis.

Considering that the SP_DropTables job was not successful, we have to ensure that data gets successfully cleared out of tier 1 before attempting to re-import any data.
Can we have the customer run the latest available version of the SP_DropTables job? This should resolve the FK issue for the SP_DropTables job and allow tier 1 to be cleared out. If the SP_DropTables job successfully runs,  have them re-run bulk import.

If FK issue continues, please provided updated logs, including the job for SP_DropTables.

[DevOps CommentId:11139700]

On Escalation Ticket # 00425524 the new comment has been added: Hi, customer confirmed that they've added it from instant jobs, but issue still persists.

To add some context, maybe that's important, they have 2 servers to run Sharepoint related scans.

JOB_1-SPSEEK_SystemScans.xml and JOB_4-SPSEEK_BulkImport.xml are on the Y0185-APP0443-S server (they are running an SDD POC on this server).

JOB_2-SPAA_SystemScans.xml and JOB_5-SPAA_BulkImport.xml are from the A0185-APP2357-S server.

Build 11.6.0.72 on Y0185-APP0443-S

Build 11.6.0.113 on A0185-APP2357-S 

Job .xml from both servers uploaded to SP.

I've suggested to upgrade Y0185-APP0443-S to 11.6.0.113, waiting for customer to book a meeting.
